The U.S.-Africa Leaders Summit is scheduled to take place in Washington, DC from December 13-15, 2022. The summit aims to highlight the United States' commitment to Africa and emphasize the importance of U.S.-Africa relations. The event will focus on various areas of cooperation, including economic engagement, democracy, human rights, addressing the impact of COVID-19 and future pandemics, regional and global health, food security, peace and security, climate crisis, and diaspora ties. The summit will involve collaboration between African governments, civil society, diaspora communities in the U.S., and the private sector to strengthen the shared vision for the future of U.S.-Africa relations.